---
@META
dir: src/hooks
updated: 2026-03-18
files: 2
stack: React 18, TypeScript

@EXPORTS
use-reduced-motion.ts: useReducedMotion — hook detecting OS prefers-reduced-motion setting
use-performance-check.ts: usePerformanceCheck — hook detecting device performance (CPU, RAM, GPU, mobile)

@FUNCTIONS
useReducedMotion() → boolean
  purpose: return true if user has OS-level reduced motion preference
  side-effects: event (MediaQueryList listener)
  called-by: animation components

usePerformanceCheck() → boolean
  purpose: return true if device has good performance (desktop, WebGL, 4+ cores, 4+ GB RAM)
  side-effects: none
  called-by: glass effect components (FluidGlass, FluidGlassSimple)

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: none
external: react (useEffect, useState)

@STANDARDS
- Both hooks are "use client" components
- Default to false on server-side rendering
- usePerformanceCheck gates heavy visual effects (glass morphism, 3D)
---
